Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky Increases Position in Nordson Corporation (NASDAQ:NDSN)

Posted by Renee Johnson on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 

Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky raised its stake in shares of Nordson Corporation (NASDAQ:NDSN) by 1.0% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 12,120 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 120 shares during the period. Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky’s holdings in Nordson Corporation were worth $1,489,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other large investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Motley Fool Wealth Management LLC acquired a new stake in Nordson Corporation during the first quarter valued at approximately $252,000. Sei Investments Co. increased its stake in shares of Nordson Corporation by 5.9% in the first quarter. Sei Investments Co. now owns 25,162 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $3,091,000 after buying an additional 1,407 shares during the last quarter. FMR LLC purchased a new stake in shares of Nordson Corporation during the first quarter worth about $44,110,000. Vanguard Group Inc. increased its stake in shares of Nordson Corporation by 6.1% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 4,396,104 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $540,018,000 after buying an additional 251,861 shares during the last quarter. Finally, Bank of Montreal Can increased its stake in shares of Nordson Corporation by 6.4% in the first quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 12,633 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $1,553,000 after buying an additional 765 shares during the last quarter. 66.04% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 




Shares of Nordson Corporation (NDSN) opened at 123.98 on Friday. The company has a 50-day moving average price of $119.53 and a 200-day moving average price of $120.46. Nordson Corporation has a 52 week low of $85.93 and a 52 week high of $131.49. The stock has a market cap of $7.15 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 26.13 and a beta of 1.34. 


 Get Nordson Corporation alerts:



Nordson Corporation (NASDAQ:NDSN) last released its earnings results on Monday, May 22nd. The industrial products company reported $1.35 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $1.30 by $0.05. The business had revenue of $496.14 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $470.12 million. Nordson Corporation had a return on equity of 33.39% and a net margin of 14.43%. The business’s quarterly revenue was up 13.4% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter last year, the business posted $1.23 earnings per share. Equities analysts anticipate that Nordson Corporation will post $5.40 EPS for the current year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky Increases Position in Nordson Corporation (NASDAQ:NDSN)” was first published by BNB Daily and is the property of of BNB Daily. If you are viewing this piece of content on another website, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of international copyright & trademark laws. The legal version of this piece of content can be accessed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/22/teachers-retirement-system-of-the-state-of-kentucky-buys-120-shares-of-nordson-corporation-nasdaqndsn-updated.html. 
NDSN has been the topic of a number of recent analyst reports. Zacks Investment Research raised shares of Nordson Corporation from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $137.00 price target on the stock in a report on Thursday, April 6th. BidaskClub raised shares of Nordson Corporation from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating in a research note on Tuesday, June 27th. Finally, Wellington Shields raised shares of Nordson Corporation from a “hold” rating to a “gradually accumulate” rating in a research note on Friday, June 2nd. Six analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and seven have issued a buy rating to the company. The company has an average rating of “Buy” and an average target price of $115.50.
About Nordson Corporation
Nordson Corporation engineers, manufactures and markets differentiated products and systems used to dispense, apply and control adhesives, coatings, polymers, sealants, biomaterials, and other fluids, to test and inspect for quality, and to treat and cure surfaces. The Company’s segments include Adhesive Dispensing Systems, Advanced Technology Systems and Industrial Coating Systems. 

 
